        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 7:18PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 718 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Great Barrington, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Great Barrington, Sheffield, Housatonic, New Marlborough, Monterey,
Alford, Tyringham, Hartsville, Egremont Plain, Newsboy Statue, Van
Deusenville, Brookside, Southfield, Belcher Square, Berkshire
Heights, North Egremont, South Egremont, and Hephzibah Heights.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
